column1: purpose: to see why we are getting slower uptake of CO than previously comparing different growth media and 1YCM to see if salt solution messed everything up
Media used for rinse and formulation steps was 1YCM PCG 10/20/15 with varying levels of Na2S and CYS (1mL -> 3mL of each)
9:20 am combined 3'A,B,C,D in an oakridge tube and put in beckman cent. for 15minutes at 5000rpm and 4C
Rinsed with 20mL of 1YCM with 2mL reducing agent
9:45 cells centrifuged in rotanna for 15min at 6000rcf and 4C
Cells placed in vacuum chamber at 25inHg at 11:30.
All tubes placed in respective RH bottles
RH bottles flushed with Argon at 10psi for 10minutes
Bottles placed in anaerobic chamber at 2:30.
**Note: Samples 4 and 6 had some kind of particulate floating around, with 6 having more than 4.
**Note: Tube C burst under pressure when it was being flushed with syngas
Tubes A-F rehydrated with 4mL of 1YCM with 2mL of added reducing agent
Tubes G-J rehydrated with 4mL of 1YCM with 4mL of added reducing agent
Tubes K-O rehydrated with 4mL of 1YCM with 6mL of added reducing agent
All tubes flushed with syngas for 2min at 10psi.
All tubes placed in shaker at 2:15 at 50 rpm and 37C
We also tested the pH of the different 1YCM types:
**Note: Tubes A-L (besides C) were all sampled at 2:15 PM
**Note: Tubes M, N, and O were sampled at 3:05 PM
